cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the credibility of web search engines, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). It also touches upon the issue of cyber security (cs.CR) and the potential use of machine learning algorithms (cs.SI) to improve credibility measures. Finally, it discusses the broader societal implications of credibility in web search engines, which could fall under the category of cyber ethics (cs.CY).
